---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="about" description="About n0brains — what we are, why we exist, and how the signal pipeline works.">
  <section class="about-section">
    <h1>about // n0brains</h1>

    <p>
      <strong>n0brains</strong> is a crypto signal API. Raw data goes in. Actionable signals come out.
    </p>

    <p>
      12 watchers monitor Telegram, blockchains, exchanges, government filings, and social media
      around the clock. An on-device LLM classifies every event, cross-references it across sources,
      and scores it for confidence — before the opportunity disappears.
    </p>

    <p>
      You get the signal. You decide what to do with it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section" style="margin-top: 48px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding-top: 48px;">
    <h1>why this exists</h1>

    <p>
      The best crypto signals aren't locked behind $500/month paywalls or exclusive Discord groups.
      They're hiding in plain sight: on-chain flows, whale wallets, funding rates, government filings,
      a dozen free data sources. The edge isn't the data — it's <strong>connecting it fast enough to act</strong>.
    </p>

    <p>
      Most people can't watch 12 sources at once. Most people can't cross-reference a whale alert
      against a funding rate spike and a Senate committee vote in the 90 seconds before the market
      moves. A machine can.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Zero paid data dependencies.</strong> Every source in the pipeline is free and public.
      If one goes down or starts charging, we replace it. The product is the synthesis, not the data.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section" style="margin-top: 48px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding-top: 48px;">
    <h1>how it works</h1>

    <p>
      <strong>1. Collect.</strong> 12 watchers scrape Telegram, RSS, blockchains, exchanges, and social media around the clock.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>2. Classify.</strong> An on-device LLM tags every event with direction, confidence, and asset scope. No external API calls. No latency. No censorship.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>3. Corroborate.</strong> The signal processor cross-references multiple sources. A whale alert backed by a funding rate spike and a news headline scores higher than any single source alone.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>4. Deliver.</strong> Signals hit your system via REST API, WebSocket, or Webhook — within seconds of detection. Free tier gets 15-minute delay. Pro gets real-time.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section" style="margin-top: 48px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding-top: 48px;">
    <h1>for agents</h1>

    <p>
      n0brains was built for autonomous trading agents first, humans second.
      The API is the product. There is no dashboard. There is no app.
    </p>

    <p>
      If you run an OpenClaw agent, a custom bot, or any system that needs crypto intelligence
      piped in programmatically — this is for you. Point your agent at the endpoint, give it your
      API key, and let it trade.
    </p>

    <p>
      Free tier: 60 requests/min, 15-minute signal delay. Enough to evaluate the data quality before you commit.<br />
      Pro tier: 600 requests/min, real-time signals, WebSocket stream, webhooks. $49.99/month. No tiers above it. No upsells.
    </p>
  </section>

  <p style="margin-top: 48px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
    // Think Less, Trade More<br />
    // brain not required
  </p>
</BaseLayout>